The fix is complete. Here's a summary of the changes made:

### Changes Applied

1. **Line 2** — Added `ToolbarContent` to the import from `@patternfly/react-core`:
   ```tsx
   // Before
   import { Toolbar, ToolbarProps } from '@patternfly/react-core';
   // After
   import { Toolbar, ToolbarContent, ToolbarProps } from '@patternfly/react-core';
   ```

2. **Line 22** — Wrapped `Toolbar` children in a `ToolbarContent` component, destructuring `children` from `props`:
   ```tsx
   // Before
   () => props => <Toolbar {...propHelpers.toolbarProps} {...props} />,
   // After
   () => ({ children, ...rest }) => <Toolbar {...propHelpers.toolbarProps} {...rest}><ToolbarContent>{children}</ToolbarContent></Toolbar>,
   ```

This satisfies the migration rule `sd-cf-toolbar-toolbar-req-content` which requires `<Toolbar>` to contain at least one `<ToolbarContent>` child. The `children` are destructured out of `props` so they aren't spread onto `<Toolbar>` and are instead passed as children of `<ToolbarContent>`. No unrelated code was changed and no cleanup was needed beyond the import addition.

